                     <title type="Complete.">II. Mälkǝʾa Mikaʾel “Image of Michael”</title>
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipit and heading of the texts; names of the donors.</rubric>
                     <incipit defective="false">Fol. 102va, l. 6:  መልክአ፡ ሚካኤል። ሰላም፡ ለዝክረ፡ ስምከ፡ ምስለ፡ ስመ፡ ልዑል፡ ዘተሳተፈ፡ ወልደ፡ ያሬድ፡ ሔኖክ፡ በከመ፡ ጸሐፈ፡ ሶበ፡ እጼውዕ፡ ስመከ፡ ከሢትየ፡ አፈ፡ ራዳኤ[sic]፡ ምንዱባን፡ ሚካኤል፡ በከመ፡ ታለምድ፡ ዘልፈ።<foreign xml:lang="en">[Fol. 102va, line 6] Effigy of Mikaˀel. Hail to the memory of your name which is associated with the High, helper of Yared and Ḥenok as it was written, I invoke your name through the mouth, Mikaˀel, you used to be perpetually the helper of these ones in trouble.</foreign>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit defective="false">Fol. 105vb, l. 2:  ሰላ[ም]፡ ለከ፡ ቅድመ፡ እግዚእከ፡ ስግድ፡ ዘበአድንኖ፡ ሰአሎ፡ ከመ፡ ይባርከነ፡ ሰፊሆ፡ የማኖ። አምላከ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዕቀበኒ፡ ወአድኅነኒ፡ እምካራ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ለዓለ[መ]፡ ዓለ[ም]፡ አሜን።<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
